2. **Direct SoA parsing** - no intermediate Row structs, parse directly to column vectors
3. **Permutation-based sorting** - avoids expensive string moves during sort
4. **Dictionary encoding at parse time** - reduces memory footprint by 75% for low-cardinality columns
5. **Fast date parsing** - manual arithmetic instead of mktime (10-100x faster)
6. **Buffered writes** - 1MB buffers reduce write() syscalls by 99%

